Key Match Events: The Bucks ran away in the second quarter with a 27-9 run to close the half.
Giannis Antetokounmpo had 25 points, 16 rebounds and eight assists.
Damian Lillard added 26 points, five rebounds and eight assists.
Victor Wembanyama was limited to just 10 points, 10 rebounds and three blocks.
Keldon Johnson had a team-high 24 points off the bench for the Spurs.
Pre-Game Insights: The Spurs entered with two losses in a row, including a 114-110 loss to the Chicago Bulls on Monday.
The Bucks were back at home after a one-game trip in Toronto.
Victor Wembanyama was limited to just 10 points, 10 rebounds and three blocks.
The Bucks did a fantastic job at denying him the ball, with just 10 shots in total.
Khris Middleton will no longer start for the Bucks and officially come off the bench moving forward.
Post-Match Reflections: Giannis Antetokounmpo had an impressive performance with 25 points, 16 rebounds and eight assists.
Damian Lillard added 26 points, five rebounds and eight assists, contributing significantly to the win.
